HEADWORD: Holothurian
<hw>Hol`o*thu"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Belonging to the Holothurioidea.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>One of the Holothurioidea.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Some of the species of Holothurians are called
<stype>sea cucumbers</stype>, <stype>sea slugs</stype>,
<stype>trepang</stype>, and <stype>b⟦ecir⟧che de m⟦egrave⟧r</stype>.
Many are used as food, esp. by the Chinese. See
<er>Trepang</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Holothurioidea</ent>⟦br⟧
